<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbf38e21a-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s11114"><num value="11114">§ 11114.</num><heading> Guidelines of Secretary</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary may establish, after notice and opportunity for comment, such voluntary guidelines as may assist the professional review bodies in meeting the standards described in <ref href="/us/usc/t42/s11112/a">section 11112(a) of this title</ref>.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idbf38e21b-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/99/660/tIV/s414">Pub. L. 99–660, title IV, § 414</ref>, <date date="1986-11-14">Nov. 14, 1986</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/100/3787">100 Stat. 3787</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
